    "lang": "fr",
    "state": "Published",
    "description": "<strong>Aim:</strong> The Swiss Agency for Development and Cooperation (SDC) has mandated the SNSF and its Croatian counterpart, the Croatian Science Foundation (CSF), to issue a call for Joint Research Projects (JRPs), conducted within the <strong>Croatian-Swiss Research Programme 2017 – 2023 (CSRP)</strong>. The initiative pursues the aims to further the integration and cooperation of Croatian researchers within international networks, to facilitate the exchange of knowledge and know-how among researchers, and to develop specific expertise at the CSF by running an exchange programme with the SNSF. The JRP enables scientists from Croatia to form consortia with scientists from Switzerland and to explore shared research questions in all scientific disciplines. Reciprocal visits and short stays of several weeks are envisaged within the context of the JRP. Overall budget is 4 MCHF, with the aim of 10-12 projects to be funded.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>Funding and duration:</strong><br>\r\nFunding (amount): max. CHF 400,000 CHF per project, funded jointly by Switzerland and Croatia (max. 50% of the grant may go to the Swiss partner)<br>\r\nDuration: generally up to 3 years (6 months extension possible if no additional funds are required)<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<strong>Deadlines:</strong><br>\r\nSubmission deadline: January 19<sup>th</sup>  2018<br>\r\nApplication: on <a href=\"https://www.mysnf.ch/login.aspx?returnurl=%2fdefault.aspx\">mySNF</a> platform<br>\r\n<br>\r\nFor more information: please have a look at <a href=\"http://www.snf.ch/en/funding/programmes/enlargement-contributions/croatia/Pages/default.aspx\">SNSF website</a> or contact the <a href=\"mailto:research@epfl\">Research Office</a><br>\r\n ",
