    "lang": "en",
    "state": "Published",
    "description": "<p>SCCER-FURIES is proud to support for the second time the Eurotech PhD School due to be held at the EPFL from 5 to 16 of Februrary 2018. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nThe Swiss Competence Center for Energy Research focused on Power grids (SCCER-FURIES) aims to enable the energy transition in Switzerland by bridging the gap between academics and the industry and transfer knowledge and technology. The development of capacities particularly of the young scientists is one of its main pillars of actions and their support to participation to key training activities contributes significantly to this purpose. Eurotech PhD school is a high-level events fully aligned with the focus of SCCER-FURIES. It balances theory and practice and provides methodological approaches to address multi-disciplinary energy-related challenges. Therefore, thanks to the collaboration between Eurotech 2018 and SCCER-FURIES, the registration fees of the school are waved for all the SCCER-FURIES PhD students.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<a href=\"https://eurotech.epfl.ch/home\">Full Program</a></p>",
